      "message": "The SkSharedMutex uses the SK_RELEASE_SHARED_CAPABILITY annotation which is correct for the mutex. I would like to have the mutex be the source of truth. The difference is that the mutex is a \"capability\" while the Sk_SCOPED_CAPABILTY is a \"fact\". The main reason for the scoped things behaving this way is that they can handle more than one mutex which could be a mixture of exclusive and shared.",
